.\" Man page for pipefetch
.TH PIPEFETCH 1 "2026-07-18" "0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pipefetch \- HTTP client for shell pipelines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pipefetch
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] \fI\,COMMAND\/\fR [\fI\,ARGS\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
pipefetch is an HTTP client designed for shell pipelines.
It supports GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE requests, JSON extraction,
pipeline chaining, environment variable interpolation, auth profiles,
and YAML collection files.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B get \fI\,URL\/\fR
Send a GET request.
.TP
.B post \fI\,URL\/\fR \fI\,BODY\/\fR
Send a POST request with JSON body.
.TP
.B put \fI\,URL\/\fR \fI\,BODY\/\fR
Send a PUT request with JSON body.
.TP
.B patch \fI\,URL\/\fR \fI\,BODY\/\fR
Send a PATCH request with JSON body.
.TP
.B delete \fI\,URL\/\fR
Send a DELETE request.
.TP
.B auth add \fI\,NAME\/\fR --auth-type \fI\,TYPE\/\fR --value \fI\,VALUE\/\fR
Add an auth profile.
.TP
.B auth list
List auth profiles.
.TP
.B auth remove \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Remove an auth profile.
.TP
.B run \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Run a YAML collection file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \--status
Print only the status line.
.TP
.B \--headers
Print only response headers.
.TP
.B \--raw
Print raw response body.
.TP
.B \--json
Machine-readable JSON output.
.TP
.B \--extract \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Extract a JSON value using dot notation (e.g. .id, .users[0].name).
.TP
.B \--auth \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Use the specified auth profile.
.TP
.B \--dry-run
Print what would be sent without making the request.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Simple GET request:
pipefetch get https://httpbin.org/get
.TP
POST with body:
pipefetch post https://httpbin.org/post '{"name":"Alice"}'
.TP
Extract a field:
pipefetch get /users --extract .name
.TP
Chain requests via pipe:
pipefetch get /repo --extract .owner.login | pipefetch get "/users/{.}"
.TP
Use env vars:
pipefetch get "https://api.example.com/${TOKEN}/users"
.TP
Run a collection:
pipefetch run examples/demo.yaml
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/pipefetch/config.yaml
Configuration file (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/pipefetch/config.yaml
Configuration file (macOS).
